# [osTicket installation on Ubuntu Server VM]

Date: [06/2026]
Status: [completed]

---

## Overview
osTicket is an open source, self-hosted support ticketing system used to manage, organize, and archive support requests. 
osTicket provides a web-based interface for creating, tracking, and resolving tickets, simulating a real-world help desk environment for training and documentation purposes.

---

## Environment
- Device: [zeroq-VM (Workstation1)]
- OS: [Ubuntu Server 22.04 LTS (64-bit)]
- IP Address: [private]

---

## Steps
1. [open VMware on workstation and power on Ubuntu Server VM (ensure network adapter is set to bridged for network-wide availability)]
2. [verify VM IP address by entering: ip a | take note of VM IP address to access osTicket through workstation1]
3. [ensure the VM is up-to-date by entering: sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y]
4. [install Apache web server by entering: sudo apt install apache2 -y]
5. [install MySQL database server by entering: sudo apt install mysql-server -y]
6. [install PHP and required extensions by entering: sudo apt install php php-mysqli php-gd php-xml php-mbstring php-intl php-apcu php-imap php-json php-curl -y]
7. [download osTicket v1.18.4 by entering: cd /tmp && wget https://github.com/osTicket/osTicket/releases/download/v1.18.4/osTicket-v1.18.4.zip]
8. [unzip and extract osTicket to Apache web directory by entering: sudo unzip /tmp/osTicket-v1.18.4.zip -d /var/www/html/osticket]
9. [set correct permissions and configure the osTicket config file by entering:]
    - sudo chown -R www-data:www-data /var/www/html/osticket
    - sudo cp /var/www/html/osticket/upload/include/ost-sampleconfig.php /var/www/html/osticket/upload/include/ost-config.php
    - sudo chmod 0666 /var/www/html/osticket/upload/include/ost-config.php
10. [set up MySQL database by entering: sudo mysql, then run the following commands:]
    - CREATE DATABASE osticket;
    - CREATE USER 'osticket'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'password';
    - GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON osticket.* TO 'osticket'@'localhost';
    - FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
    - EXIT;
11. [access the osTicket installer in browser at: (private IP/osticket/upload) and complete setup]
12. [configure helpdesk name, admin credentials, and database settings through the web installer]

